I was updating some tools when I noticed what appears to be an extra, superfluous stat at the end of the sort_orders list inside each teams rankings data. I am wondering if I am simply not unpacking the data correctly or if TBA is just being overly generous.

For example, I get back the following from a get_event_rankings() API call:

{‘extra_stats_info’: [{‘name’: ‘Total Ranking Points’, ‘precision’: 0.0}],
‘rankings’: [{‘dq’: 0,
‘extra_stats’: [31.0],
‘matches_played’: 11,
‘qual_average’: None,
‘rank’: 1,
‘record’: {‘losses’: 1, ‘ties’: 1, ‘wins’: 9},
‘sort_orders’: [2.82, 0.82, 53.27, 19.64, 4.0, 0.0],
‘team_key’: ‘frc3128’},
…
,
‘sort_order_info’: [{‘name’: ‘Ranking Score’, ‘precision’: 2},
{‘name’: ‘Avg Coop’, ‘precision’: 2},
{‘name’: ‘Avg Match’, ‘precision’: 2},
{‘name’: ‘Avg Auto’, ‘precision’: 2},
{‘name’: ‘Avg Stage’, ‘precision’: 2}]}

There are 6 values in the sort_orders list but only 5 entries in the parent’s sort_order_info. Can anyone help me noodle out what the 6th value is intended for?
